oduction of notions of violence and solidarity. Himika Bhattacharya centers the women’s narratives as a site of knowledge—beyond love and beyond violence. This book shows how women on the margins of tribe and caste know both, love and violence, as agents wishing to re-shape discourses of caste, tribe and community.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jan 2021) 0aDalit womenzIndiazLahūlxSocial conditions. 0aDalit womenzIndiazLahūlxSocial conditions. 0aWomenxViolence againstzIndiazLahūl. 0aWomenxViolence againstzIndiazLahūl. 0aWomenzIndiazLahūlxSocial conditions. 0aWomenzIndiazLahūlxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017z978311066609040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081358957240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813589572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813589572.jpg  a978-3-11-066609-0  RUP eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK